sustainable technology.

21:15.360 --> 21:18.250
So, these kids... the work force...

21:18.250 --> 21:20.260
- Mm-hmm.
- Are they the ones

21:20.260 --> 21:22.260
from the tornado that I saw on TV?

21:22.260 --> 21:24.280
Some of them.

21:24.280 --> 21:27.280
We're preparing for
when The Future comes.

21:27.280 --> 21:29.300
The Future?

21:29.300 --> 21:30.450
You have a copy of The Ladder.

21:30.450 --> 21:33.430
It explains it all in there.

21:33.430 --> 21:36.250
Wow, so do you guys always do that?

21:36.250 --> 21:37.470
You know, go in after a disaster?

21:37.470 --> 21:39.340
You know, we do what we can,

21:39.340 --> 21:43.320
and hope to do more as we grow.

21:43.320 --> 21:45.480
Here, I want to show you something.

21:50.270 --> 21:52.370
[door opens, toilet flushes]

21:52.370 --> 21:54.250
You're up early.

21:54.250 --> 21:56.340
How long has your
refrigerator been broken?

21:56.340 --> 21:58.420
I tried calling. They never came.

21:58.420 --> 22:00.460
Oh, so you haven't had any
fresh food in what...

22:00.460 --> 22:03.280
I'm fine. I eat.

22:03.280 --> 22:04.400
What is that?

22:04.400 --> 22:07.330
I found a 24-hour
vegetarian place nearby.

22:07.330 --> 22:10.270
- South Indian...
- You eat that for breakfast?

22:10.270 --> 22:12.350
Not much else was open. I had to...

22:12.350 --> 22:14.430
Doesn't look too bad, actually.

22:14.430 --> 22:17.260
Looks like dog food.

22:17.260 --> 22:19.410
It's lentils and rice.

22:19.410 --> 22:22.470
You could at least have
some plain rice to...

22:22.470 --> 22:26.390
To soak things up.

22:26.390 --> 22:28.450
[grunts]

22:28.450 --> 22:31.260
A little early?

22:31.260 --> 22:33.340
Late somewhere.

22:33.340 --> 22:36.480
I have no idea how you trick
people into joining you.

22:36.480 --> 22:39.260
I mean, you live in tents.

22:39.260 --> 22:41.310
You eat that... Tents?

22:41.310 --> 22:44.480
That was... that was
one summer, years ago.

22:44.480 --> 22:46.440
We have a beautiful campus now.

22:46.440 --> 22:49.290
Mm... your father had you in a tent

22:49.290 --> 22:50.440
- in the middle of winter...
- [chuckles]

22:50.440 --> 22:52.350
And I was the unfit parent.

22:52.350 --> 22:53.450
You know, we're even expanding.

22:53.450 --> 22:55.370
I was on the news the
other day about...

22:55.370 --> 22:57.280
- Oh, that's right.
- Some of our new programs.

22:57.280 --> 23:01.310
- You're a big shot.
- No, I'm just saying...

23:01.310 --> 23:04.290
I'm just saying I draw a salary.

23:04.290 --> 23:05.430
A decent one.

23:05.430 --> 23:08.290
Enough to afford a nice place for you.

23:08.290 --> 23:09.470
Old folks home.

23:09.470 --> 23:12.320
Assisted living.

23:12.320 --> 23:16.310
What if I say no?

23:16.310 --> 23:20.280
They're gonna kick you
out of this place.

23:20.280 --> 23:23.460
All right, you want to
show me a nice place...

23:23.460 --> 23:26.360
Fine.

23:26.360 --> 23:30.350
Really?

23:30.350 --> 23:32.260
That's great, Mom.

23:32.260 --> 23:33.410
One condition:

23:33.410 --> 23:36.410
Have a drink with me.

23:38.420 --> 23:42.410
I can't do that,

23:42.410 --> 23:45.360
and it is horrible that
you would ask me to.

23:45.360 --> 23:46.410
[scoffs]

23:46.410 --> 23:48.430
Fine.

23:48.430 --> 23:50.400
I'm not going. I'll stay here.

23:50.400 --> 23:52.350
You wanna die on the street?

23:52.350 --> 23:53.470
I wanna die here

23:53.470 --> 23:56.470
in my own home.

24:01.320 --> 24:04.320
<i>[dark music]</i>

24:04.320 --> 24:12.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:16.410 --> 24:19.330
Do you promise you'll go?

24:19.330 --> 24:22.330
On your father's grave.

24:22.330 --> 24:30.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:39.410 --> 24:42.380
- [bourbon pouring]
- [scoffs]

24:42.380 --> 24:45.280
So what happens if you do
something that you're, like,

24:45.280 --> 24:46.450
not supposed to do,

24:46.450 --> 24:48.290
like hanging out with me?

24:48.290 --> 24:51.310
Do you get punished?

24:51.310 --> 24:54.480
Or is there some sort of
public flogging or something?

24:54.480 --> 24:57.380
- [laughs]
- No.

24:57.380 --> 25:01.260
It's not like that. Nobody whips you.

25:01.260 --> 25:03.320
It's more like...

25:03.320 --> 25:06.260
I'd whip myself.

25:06.260 --> 25:08.370
- [laughs]
- Wait, that's really weird.

25:08.370 --> 25:11.450
- Literally?
- No, not literally.

25:11.450 --> 25:17.360
Um... I'd just feel really bad.

25:17.360 --> 25:20.380
Like...

25:20.380 --> 25:24.310
lost and...

25:24.310 --> 25:27.410
It's hard to explain to someone outside.

25:27.410 --> 25:31.270
Try.

25:31.270 --> 25:32.450
Okay, this is gonna sound preachy,

25:32.450 --> 25:36.380
- but you're asking me, so...
- Yeah, I want to know.

25:36.380 --> 25:38.310
Dr. Steven Meyer,

25:38.310 --> 25:43.310
he says the adolescent brain is HS.

25:45.320 --> 25:48.250
Hypersensitized.

25:48.250 --> 25:50.340
It means

25:50.340 --> 25:53.470
- vulnerable to... you know.
- Bad influences.

25:53.470 --> 25:56.380
You're not bad. You're just...

25:56.380 --> 25:58.400
- ignorant.
- Ignorant?

25:58.400 --> 26:01.390
Of the right way to live your life.

26:01.390 --> 26:03.270
That's sort of offensive.

26:03.270 --> 26:04.470
It's not meant to be.

26:04.470 --> 26:07.290
Wait, so when you guys do
that weird praying thing...

26:07.290 --> 26:09.280
- I don't think it's weird.
- Are you... no, but are you,

26:09.280 --> 26:10.430
like, fending off the ignorance?

26:10.430 --> 26:14.350
You're, like, protecting
yourself from me?

26:14.350 --> 26:18.340
- I bet you pray too.
- No, I don't, actually.

26:18.340 --> 26:21.320
Really? Even before a test?

26:21.320 --> 26:23.370
Or when you're really
stressed out about something?

26:23.370 --> 26:27.290
You don't go, "Please,
please, let this be okay"?

26:27.290 --> 26:30.390
- Yeah.
- Or when your dad died.

26:34.480 --> 26:37.480
Sorry.

26:37.480 --> 26:40.380
That's okay.

26:40.380 --> 26:42.430
People just don't really talk about it.

26:42.430 --> 26:46.360
That's all.

26:46.360 --> 26:48.330
But yeah, I mean, I guess I do that.

26:48.330 --> 26:51.280
That's not really praying though.

26:51.280 --> 26:52.380
Why not?

26:52.380 --> 26:55.300
Because I don't believe in God.

26:55.300 --> 26:58.300
Then who are you talking to?

27:04.390 --> 27:06.340
The library's only open
for a couple more hours.

27:06.340 --> 27:07.480
Right, and you still can't.

27:07.480 --> 27:10.390
No, um, but hey, if you could, like,

27:10.390 --> 27:14.370
pray to get my power
turned back on then...

27:14.370 --> 27:16.450
I mean, if you could do that,

27:16.450 --> 27:19.360
who knows, right?

27:29.280 --> 27:32.250
After lunch, our residents
turn this into a game room,

27:32.250 --> 27:34.440
and after dinner, Alice, our
occupational therapist,

27:34.440 --> 27:36.330
teaches moonlight Tai Chi.

27:36.330 --> 27:38.360
Tai Chi, Ma, that sounds lovely.

27:38.360 --> 27:40.360
What about her?

27:40.360 --> 27:43.270
She ain't doing any Tai Chi. Mother.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.380
She ain't buying any
green bananas either.

27:45.380 --> 27:48.380
[laughs]

27:54.400 --> 27:55.460
Would you be interested in

27:55.460 --> 27:57.410
a semi-private apartment or private?

27:57.410 --> 27:59.330
- Private, definitely.
- Excellent.

27:59.330 --> 28:01.350
I'll just go ahead and get
started on the paperwork.

28:01.350 --> 28:03.290
Oh, nothing but the best for my son.

28:03.290 --> 28:04.470
He runs a cult.

28:04.470 --> 28:07.290
No, it's not a cult.

28:07.290 --> 28:09.300
Ah, it's okay. They say things.

28:09.300 --> 28:10.380
Oh, I'm not demented.

28:10.380 --> 28:12.410
If anyone's demented, it's my son.

28:12.410 --> 28:15.410
- The cult leader.
- I need you to stop, Ma.

28:15.410 --> 28:17.450
- Maybe I should just...
- We're a spiritual movement.

28:17.450 --> 28:19.420
That kidnapped a five-year-old boy.

28:19.420 --> 28:22.250
No. No one was kidnapped.

28:22.250 --> 28:25.270
- My dad took me away...
- And had the sense to leave.

28:25.270 --> 28:27.430
- He came back to me.
- And drank himself to death.

28:27.430 --> 28:30.390
You were the stubborn one.
You stuck with that quack.

28:30.390 --> 28:32.390
Please don't call him that.

28:32.390 --> 28:35.270
All right, he's the only
real parent I ever had.

28:35.270 --> 28:37.330
A quack for a quack.

28:37.330 --> 28:39.350
Quack! Quack!

28:39.350 --> 28:40.480
Quack!

28:40.480 --> 28:42.370
Quack!

28:42.370 --> 28:44.290
Quack!

28:44.290 --> 28:46.410
Quack! Quack!

28:46.410 --> 28:48.330
Make that noise one more time

28:48.330 --> 28:50.340
I will let you die like a
fucking dog on the street

28:50.340 --> 28:51.440
because that's what you deserve!

28:51.440 --> 28:53.390
Mr. Roberts, please!

28:53.390 --> 28:55.440
[gasps]

29:02.350 --> 29:04.260
[sighs]

29:09.699 --> 29:12.430
Why won't she unburden?
It makes no sense.

29:12.430 --> 29:14.370
Half the world is in denial, Sarah.

29:14.370 --> 29:15.460
More than half.

29:15.460 --> 29:18.480
Denial is a comfy house,

29:18.480 --> 29:20.460
but it's made of glass,

29:20.460 --> 29:22.370
and when it shatters...

29:22.370 --> 29:24.250
I need to talk to Eddie about it.

29:24.250 --> 29:25.410
He's not 7R.

29:25.410 --> 29:28.310
Well, neither are you,
and neither is Nicole.

29:28.310 --> 29:30.260
You know, it really upsets me.

29:30.260 --> 29:32.250
Am I the only one that
adheres to the system?

29:32.250 --> 29:34.480
- Hey.
- [groans]

29:34.480 --> 29:37.310
Oh, can I just get a
little bit of that?

29:37.310 --> 29:39.280
Not with my grandbaby in there.

29:39.280 --> 29:42.330
Mom, it's not 1950. It's
not gonna kill the baby.

29:42.330 --> 29:44.480
No, you're right, Gab, I shouldn't.

29:44.480 --> 29:47.400
I've got your casserole dish
over there, by the way.

29:47.400 --> 29:50.370
- Thanks for that.
- Oh, honey, it was my pleasure.

29:50.370 --> 29:52.390
Whatever I can do to help.

29:52.390 --> 29:54.380
I can't imagine what
you were going through

29:54.380 --> 29:57.280
while Eddie was away... I
wouldn't have been able to cook.

29:57.280 --> 29:58.460
- Thanks.
- If there's anything else

29:58.460 --> 30:02.260
that we can do... oh, crap.
Those two are always fighting.

30:02.260 --> 30:05.340
You two, cut it out!

30:05.340 --> 30:08.310
- She...
- [both laugh]

30:08.310 --> 30:09.430
She is loving it.

30:09.430 --> 30:13.270
Like bringing over those
passive-agressive pot pies.

30:13.270 --> 30:14.460
She means well,

30:14.460 --> 30:17.260
and come on, you've always
been the perfect one.

30:17.260 --> 30:19.290
[clears throat]

30:19.290 --> 30:22.250
How are you guys doing?

30:22.250 --> 30:25.310
Eddie's speech yesterday was beautiful.

30:25.310 --> 30:27.370
Mm.

30:27.370 --> 30:30.340
You still have the walls up.

30:30.340 --> 30:32.370
With time you'll feel safer.

30:32.370 --> 30:35.330
They'll come down again.

30:35.330 --> 30:38.280
You know, catching Daddy
was the best thing

30:38.280 --> 30:41.380
that ever happened to us.

30:43.350 --> 30:45.350
Yeah, I transgressed once.

30:45.350 --> 30:47.290
You know that?

30:47.290 --> 30:50.360
Yeah, yeah, I know.

30:50.360 --> 30:52.360
Marriage is, um...

30:52.360 --> 30:54.450
what have you guys been together?

30:54.450 --> 30:56.330
Long time... you were kids.

30:56.330 --> 30:58.440
Same as with me and Gab.

31:00.420 --> 31:04.470
It's hard not to be tempted.

31:04.470 --> 31:08.320
New flesh.

31:08.320 --> 31:11.350
That's not exactly what, uh...

31:11.350 --> 31:13.460
But I get what you're saying.

31:13.460 --> 31:17.480
But you feel differently
when it happens to your kid,

31:17.480 --> 31:20.330
your daughter.

31:20.330 --> 31:23.450
Less compassionate.

31:23.450 --> 31:26.390
You get it?

31:26.390 --> 31:28.300
I mean, you know what it's
like when you see pain

31:28.300 --> 31:31.250
in your kids' eyes.

31:31.250 --> 31:36.410
You'd go to lengths to
take that pain away.

31:36.410 --> 31:40.280
I do know, Hank.

31:42.340 --> 31:44.450
Good.

31:44.450 --> 31:47.420
All right, here it comes.

31:47.420 --> 31:50.300
I would like to lead
the prayer tonight.

31:50.300 --> 31:52.480
I think it would be good
for me, for my family.

31:52.480 --> 31:56.340
I don't have a problem with it.

31:56.340 --> 31:58.350
All right.

31:58.350 --> 32:01.300
- I think we are good here.
- Let's eat.

32:01.300 --> 32:04.360
Together: ♪ To the top
of Huayna Picchu ♪

32:04.360 --> 32:07.350
♪ Our brave Doc Meyer climbed ♪

32:07.350 --> 32:10.350
♪ So much evil in this world that ♪

32:10.350 --> 32:13.280
♪ He promised to make right ♪

32:13.280 --> 32:16.280
♪ After many years of searching ♪

32:16.280 --> 32:18.410
♪ And nothing to be found ♪

32:18.410 --> 32:21.370
♪ The tears fell down down
down his cheekbones ♪

32:21.370 --> 32:22.470
- Got soup?
- [both chuckle]

32:22.470 --> 32:25.440
Both: ♪ Like raindrops to the ground ♪

32:25.440 --> 32:28.350
- [door opens]
- Hey, stranger.

32:28.350 --> 32:30.380
Hey.

32:30.380 --> 32:32.300
Everything all right?

32:32.300 --> 32:34.310
Yeah, I just had after-school stuff

32:34.310 --> 32:36.310
- Like what?
- Joy.

32:36.310 --> 32:39.430
He doesn't do stuff. He
doesn't do anything.

32:39.430 --> 32:41.260
[cell phone ringing]

32:41.260 --> 32:44.350
Can I please just wash my hands?

32:44.350 --> 32:47.320
Hey, I have to take this.

32:47.320 --> 32:49.320
Hey.

32:51.310 --> 32:55.300
<i>I'm drunk.</i>

32:55.300 --> 32:58.280
- Where are you?
- I'm not on 10R business.

32:58.280 --> 33:00.380
I'm in Troy,

33:00.380 --> 33:03.320
and I'm shit-faced.

33:03.320 --> 33:05.470
Okay.

33:05.470 --> 33:09.450
<i>- I'm with Brenda.</i>
- Oh, boy.

33:09.450 --> 33:13.250
Two years, 37 days
since my last slip up.

33:13.250 --> 33:14.380
It happens. Okay.

33:14.380 --> 33:16.300
Especially with the trigger of Brenda.

33:16.300 --> 33:17.440
<i>I grabbed her arm,</i>

33:17.440 --> 33:21.420
and she's just a wreck.

33:21.420 --> 33:24.370
- I could kill her with one...
- <i>Listen to me.</i>

33:24.370 --> 33:26.300
You get a cab.

33:26.300 --> 33:28.340
All right. Sleep it off.

33:28.340 --> 33:31.400
- We'll talk about it later.
- <i>I worked so hard on myself...</i>

33:31.400 --> 33:35.350
- on...
- [sighs]

33:35.350 --> 33:38.470
And one day with Brenda and
it's just all out the window.

33:38.470 --> 33:41.290
After everything that woman
has put you through.

33:41.290 --> 33:44.280
<i>- Problem...</i>
- So much pain.

33:44.280 --> 33:47.280
- [crying]
<i>- It's only natural.</i>

33:47.280 --> 33:51.260
This is just a moment. I promise.

33:51.260 --> 33:53.250
It'll pass.

33:53.250 --> 33:57.330
Hey, dinner's ready.

33:57.330 --> 34:01.280
Um, I have to go. It's dinner.

34:01.280 --> 34:03.460
- [clears throat]
- Of course, yeah.

34:03.460 --> 34:06.460
I'm fine.

34:11.340 --> 34:16.280
- Who was that?
- It's just, uh...

34:16.280 --> 34:18.280
he had a question.

34:18.280 --> 34:19.440
What, Cal?

34:19.440 --> 34:23.350
Yeah, nothing important.

34:27.280 --> 34:30.280
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:30.280 --> 34:38.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:38.280 --> 34:39.449
What the fuck are you doing here?

34:39.449 --> 34:42.340
- I'm sorry, but I need you.
- No, you come near me

34:42.340 --> 34:46.260
or my family again, I
will fucking kill you.

34:46.260 --> 34:47.409
That is not a threat.

34:47.409 --> 34:49.429
You do not know where I come from.

34:49.429 --> 34:52.429
[breathing heavy]

34:59.390 --> 35:01.470
<i>Thank you for the gifts of this bread,</i>

35:01.470 --> 35:05.380
to sustain these vessels, our bodies,

35:05.380 --> 35:09.370
so that may have the energy to
create a more beautiful world,

35:09.370 --> 35:13.340
and break through the blocks
and barriers of this life

35:13.340 --> 35:15.470
and ascend The Ladder
of Enlightenment...

35:15.470 --> 35:20.360
together: So that someday we may
be free of these earthly forms

35:20.360 --> 35:23.370
and live as Light
together in The Garden.

35:23.370 --> 35:26.250
<i>We express deepest gratitude</i>

35:26.250 --> 35:28.370
<i>this day and every day.</i>

35:28.370 --> 35:30.350
<i>We cling to this passage</i>

35:30.350 --> 35:32.480
<i>and when we have found The Ladder</i>

35:32.480 --> 35:39.290
<i>with one spirit whose name is Truth.</i>

35:39.290 --> 35:40.440
Help me

35:40.440 --> 35:44.280
see the path of Light,

35:44.280 --> 35:47.270
of right.

35:47.270 --> 35:50.250
Help me see the path

35:50.250 --> 35:53.290
of Light, of right.

35:53.290 --> 35:55.340
- [whispers]
- Help...

35:55.340 --> 35:58.340
<i>[dramatic orchestra music]</i>

35:58.340 --> 36:06.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:11.420 --> 36:14.380
Hey.

36:15.460 --> 36:19.320
Oh, wow.

36:25.420 --> 36:29.420
- [sighs]
- I'm doing everything I can here.

36:29.420 --> 36:31.310
I know.

36:31.310 --> 36:34.250
Committing to the program. To you.

36:34.250 --> 36:36.340
- I am too.
- So, why isn't this working?

36:36.340 --> 36:37.410
I don't know.

36:37.410 --> 36:39.270
You have to meet me halfway, Sarah.

36:39.270 --> 36:41.350
I am meeting you halfway.

36:41.350 --> 36:43.390
Sure, you are.

36:43.390 --> 36:46.410
Out there on the compound,

36:46.410 --> 36:48.480
family dinners, but
when it's just us...

36:48.480 --> 36:51.280
Listen, I don't know what to tell you.

36:51.280 --> 36:53.340
This is not easy for me either, Eddie,

36:53.340 --> 36:56.390
and especially when I am doing
everything that I can...

36:56.390 --> 36:58.320
Are you though?

36:58.320 --> 37:02.410
Because I don't feel you with me.

37:02.410 --> 37:05.460
Miranda Frank is here.

37:05.460 --> 37:07.390
What?

37:07.390 --> 37:11.330
And I cant stop thinking
about you and her together,

37:11.330 --> 37:14.250
and I hate it,

37:14.250 --> 37:15.400
and I know I'm supposed to be better,

37:15.400 --> 37:17.370
- but I am not.
- What is she doing...

37:17.370 --> 37:21.280
She wouldn't unburden, Eddie.

37:22.390 --> 37:25.350
- [sighs]
- And now she's here.

37:25.350 --> 37:28.320
<i>[dark music]</i>

37:28.320 --> 37:29.430
I'm not even supposed
to be telling you this.

37:29.430 --> 37:33.310
It's 7R, but how are we supposed to...

37:33.310 --> 37:41.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:48.380 --> 38:51.380
[door buzzes, opens]

38:52.450 --> 38:55.340
I'm not drinking that fucking juice.

38:55.340 --> 38:56.440
I just want you to know

38:56.440 --> 38:58.330
because I don't think you understand...

38:58.330 --> 39:00.450
I've had enough! I'm a
fucking prisoner here.

39:00.450 --> 39:02.380
The effect you are having.

39:02.380 --> 39:04.380
The horrible, horrible effect you are...

39:04.380 --> 39:07.250
Whatever is going on between you
and your husband has nothing

39:07.250 --> 39:09.280
to do with me, so work your
fucking marital problems out...

39:09.280 --> 39:10.420
You are nobody!

39:10.420 --> 39:12.340
You are nothing!

39:12.340 --> 39:15.250
You're a whore.

39:15.250 --> 39:16.410
What you are doing to me?

39:16.410 --> 39:19.420
What you have done to my family?

39:19.420 --> 39:21.290
You will stay here

39:21.290 --> 39:24.290
and complete the program.

39:24.290 --> 39:27.260
Every second of it.

39:27.260 --> 39:28.450
Drink up.

39:28.450 --> 39:30.460
- [pounding on door]
- Help!

39:30.460 --> 39:33.380
[crying and screaming]

39:33.380 --> 39:37.320
Let me out of here!

39:37.320 --> 39:39.340
Let me out!

39:45.380 --> 39:48.380
Is that better?

39:51.280 --> 39:53.330
Okay, I'll, um...

39:53.330 --> 39:56.290
[clears throat]

39:56.290 --> 39:59.390
- If you need anything.
- We talked about you.

39:59.390 --> 40:02.350
Those last years after he came back.

40:02.350 --> 40:03.470
We talked about you a lot.

40:03.470 --> 40:05.320
Mom, I don't really want to hear...

40:05.320 --> 40:08.260
He said, "Cal is our son.

40:08.260 --> 40:09.450
"Not that man's.

40:09.450 --> 40:13.440
He's ours."

40:13.440 --> 40:15.380
Keep running,

40:15.380 --> 40:19.320
but you can't escape.

40:19.320 --> 40:22.320
Once you stop trying,

40:22.320 --> 40:24.400
you'll feel better.

40:24.400 --> 40:28.310
'Cause wanting to be someone else

40:28.310 --> 40:31.270
never works.

40:33.450 --> 40:37.440
Just brings you right back here.

40:37.440 --> 40:40.440
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:40.440 --> 40:48.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:48.450 --> 40:52.360
It's too bright.

40:54.360 --> 41:02.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:02.290 --> 41:06.370
What about the guy who did this to me?

41:06.370 --> 41:08.280
We're doing everything we can

41:08.280 --> 41:11.270
to gather information on him, Mr. Cox.

41:11.270 --> 41:13.400
Well, how bout you grab that asshole

41:13.400 --> 41:15.350
and throw him in jail?

41:15.350 --> 41:17.250
Hmm?

41:17.250 --> 41:19.440
How hard is that?

41:19.440 --> 41:22.360
Do you want him in jail overnight

41:22.360 --> 41:25.310
on an assault charge,

41:25.310 --> 41:29.470
or do you want him locked
away for 30 years?

41:29.470 --> 41:33.280
The fucking animal

41:33.280 --> 41:37.270
has got my daughter.

41:37.270 --> 41:41.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:41.320 --> 41:44.470
I have three kids.

41:44.470 --> 41:47.390
You got my word.

41:47.390 --> 41:51.350
I will bring your daughter back.

41:51.350 --> 41:59.350
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:06.380 --> 42:08.260
Thank you.

42:08.260 --> 42:11.420
- For what?
- I totally saw you.

42:11.420 --> 42:13.340
You were trying to run away,

42:13.340 --> 42:16.420
but I saw you watching me.

42:16.420 --> 42:20.360
I just couldn't let you
live without light.

42:26.390 --> 42:29.440
Thank you.

42:29.440 --> 42:32.440
<i>[tense music]</i>

42:32.440 --> 42:40.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:41.370 --> 42:43.350
Hey.

42:43.350 --> 42:46.250
Hey. How you feeling?

42:46.250 --> 42:48.250
Like shit, but it'll pass.

42:48.250 --> 42:50.340
If you need to be realigned
just let me know.

42:50.340 --> 42:54.420
Uh, there's actually...

42:54.420 --> 42:58.290
something else I wanted
to talk to you about.

42:58.290 --> 43:01.290
Something that happened
in Peru with Steve.

43:01.290 --> 43:02.380
Okay.

43:02.380 --> 43:05.340
Sit down.

43:07.250 --> 43:09.450
Um...

43:12.400 --> 43:17.280
There's been a shift.

43:17.280 --> 43:20.280
Something monumental...

43:22.260 --> 43:25.380
And I'm walking around with it

43:25.380 --> 43:27.250
rattling inside me

43:27.250 --> 43:29.380
and... and I have to get it out.

43:29.380 --> 43:31.410
Even though it's 10R,

43:31.410 --> 43:34.280
- and I shouldn't disclose...
- Well, what is it?

43:34.280 --> 43:37.470
- You're worrying me.
- Steve let me know something

43:37.470 --> 43:40.480
about the final rungs
that he's receiving.

43:40.480 --> 43:44.250
They're about succession of leadership.

43:44.250 --> 43:47.430
What's next after he goes.

43:47.430 --> 43:50.270
- The Plan.
- Where's he going?

43:50.270 --> 43:52.470
- Um...
- What's wrong?

43:52.470 --> 43:54.430
The message he's receiving,

43:54.430 --> 43:56.460
uh, it's telling him

43:56.460 --> 43:59.290
that it is

43:59.290 --> 44:03.270
time to move on,

44:03.270 --> 44:05.380
and put a new leader

44:05.380 --> 44:08.290
in his place.

44:08.290 --> 44:10.400
[sighs]

44:13.430 --> 44:16.460
It's you, isn't it?

44:16.460 --> 44:19.460
Does that sound crazy?

44:21.390 --> 44:24.450
It's always been you.

44:31.400 --> 44:34.470
<i>[tense music]</i>

44:34.470 --> 44:36.420
Hey Eddie.

44:36.420 --> 44:38.330
Need help with something?

44:38.330 --> 44:39.460
Oh, what's up, Isiah?

44:39.460 --> 44:43.360
Um, I'm just supposed
to talk to Miranda.

44:43.360 --> 44:45.380
It's designated 7R.

44:45.380 --> 44:47.470
Yeah, no, I know, but, um...

44:47.470 --> 44:50.480
I'm authorized by Cal.

44:50.480 --> 44:52.390
Well, he didn't tell me.

44:52.390 --> 44:53.470
Look, I don't know, man, that's weird.

44:53.470 --> 44:57.330
It's just I'm supposed to, um...

44:57.330 --> 45:01.290
Look, it's a family matter, Isiah.

45:02.290 --> 45:04.390
Okay.

45:04.390 --> 45:08.390
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:08.390 --> 45:11.250
[sighs]

45:17.330 --> 45:20.480
Hey, Miranda, this is, uh, Eddie.

45:20.480 --> 45:23.340
Can we talk?

45:25.450 --> 45:28.450
Miranda?

45:28.450 --> 45:30.280
[door buzzes]

45:30.280 --> 45:32.450
Hey.

45:32.450 --> 45:34.370
Ah, Jesus Christ!

45:34.370 --> 45:37.420
Hey, hey. I need some help in here!

45:37.420 --> 45:39.470
Hey. Hey.

45:39.470 --> 45:42.410
Hey, need some help! Miranda, Miranda.

45:42.410 --> 45:44.480
Hey, hey, hey, Miranda. Wake up.

45:44.480 --> 45:47.470
Hey... hey. Need some help!

45:47.470 --> 45:50.371
Miranda! Miranda! Somebody!

